## Audiobook Simplifier

**Audiobook Simplifier** is a tool that creates audiobooks from text documents or ebooks using TTS (Text-to-Speech) technology.

## Description

This project transforms text documents or ebooks into audio files using TTSv2, making written content accessible in audio format.

## Installation

### Prerequisites

- **Python 3.10**: Download and install Python 3.10 for Windows. During installation, make sure to:
  - Choose to install for all users.
  - Choose to add Python to PATH.
  [Download Link](https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.10.11/python-3.10.11-amd64.exe)

- **FFmpeg**: Download and install FFmpeg and add it to the PATH environment variable.
  [Download Link](https://www.ffmpeg.org/download.html)

- **CUDA Toolkit 10.1**: Download and install CUDA Toolkit 10.1 (not 11.0+).
  [Download Link](https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-10.1-download-archive-base)

- **cuDNN v7.6.5**: Download "cuDNN v7.6.5 (November 5, 2019), for CUDA 10.1" (not cuDNN v8+), extract it, and then copy the contents of the folder to `C:\\Program Files\\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\\CUDA\\v10.1`.
  [Download Link](https://developer.nvidia.com/rdp/cudnn-archive)

- **eSpeak NG**: Download the latest 64-bit version of eSpeak NG.
  [Download Link](https://github.com/espeak-ng/espeak-ng/releases)

- **Git for Windows**: Download the latest 64-bit version of Git for Windows.
  [Download Link](https://git-scm.com/downloads/win)

